## 2. Solution Overview

ActionPilot solves the execution gap by wrapping a traditional task management system in an autonomous, agentic feedback loop. The system acts as a persistent project manager that works in the background while the user focuses on execution.

```
+----------------+      +-------------------+      +---------------------+
|   User Goal    | ---> | AI Goal Analyzer  | ---> |  AI Planning Agent  |
|  (Ambiguous)   |      | (Categorize/Risk) |      | (Actionable Tasks)  |
+----------------+      +-------------------+      +---------------------+
                                                              |
                                                              v
+----------------+      +-------------------+      +---------------------+
|   Goal Status  | <--- | Background Sweeps | <--- |   User Execution    |
| (Active/Risk)  |      |  (Risk/Standup)   |      |  & Progress Logs    |
+----------------+      +-------------------+      +---------------------+
        |
        +-------------> [High Risk (>70%)] ---> AI Recovery Agent
                                                (Optimized Plan generated)
```

The core workflow consists of the following phases:

1. **Strategic Goal Entry:** The user inputs a high-level goal, brief description, and target deadline.
2. **AI-Assisted Initialization:** The system routes the goal to the **AI Goal Analyzer Agent**, which assesses complexity, estimates effort in hours, and identifies potential risk factors.
3. **Structured Plan Generation:** The **AI Planning Agent** immediately digests the analysis and decomposes the goal into a chronological sequence of 4–7 prioritized tasks with realistic hourly estimates.
4. **Active Execution Telemetry:** The user marks tasks as completed or logs granular check-ins. During check-ins, the user provides a qualitative status update, defines their confidence level (1-5), and explicitly flags any active blockers.
5. **Autonomous Background Sweeps:** A BullMQ background worker, running periodically via Redis, sweeps active goals. It executes three background agents:
   * **Inactivity Monitor:** Alerts the user via Web Push if no progress logs are submitted within 24 hours.
   * **AI Risk Agent:** Evaluates task velocity, blocker descriptions, and confidence trends to calculate a target deadline completion probability. If the risk score exceeds 70%, the goal status transitions to `AT_RISK`.
   * **AI Standup Coach:** Generates a structured daily briefing covering completed, pending, and critical path items, suggesting daily focus areas.
6. **Dynamic Recovery Loop:** When the Risk Agent flags a goal as `AT_RISK`, the **AI Recovery Agent** is triggered. It reviews the current blockers, remaining tasks, and time constraints to formulate specific recovery suggestions and rebuild an optimized task checklist, preserving all completed tasks while restructuring pending items.

