## 6. User Workflow

The end-to-end user workflow in ActionPilot highlights the interaction between user inputs, database states, and background processes:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Client as React Client
    participant API as Express API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL DB
    participant Queue as Redis Queue
    participant Worker as BullMQ Worker
    participant Gemini as Gemini AI API

    User->>Client: Register / Login
    Client->>API: POST /auth/login
    API->>Client: Send JWT Token
    User->>Client: Input Goal Title, Desc, Deadline
    Client->>API: POST /goals
    API->>DB: Create Goal (Status: DRAFT)
    API->>Queue: Push Planning Job
    API->>Client: Goal Saved (Return ID)
    Queue->>Worker: Pull Planning Job
    Worker->>Gemini: analyzeGoal() & generatePlan()
    Gemini-->>Worker: Return JSON Analysis & Task List
    Worker->>DB: Save Tasks & AgentReport (Goal Status: PLANNED)
    Worker->>DB: Create Notification (Goal Ready)
    Worker-->>User: Push Web Notification (VAPID)
    Note over User, Client: Goal is now ACTIVE. User works on tasks.
    User->>Client: Log Progress Check-in (Text, Confidence, Blocker)
    Client->>API: POST /progress
    API->>DB: Save Progress Log
    API->>Queue: Trigger On-demand Sweep
    Queue->>Worker: Run Sweep Job
    Worker->>Gemini: evaluateRisk()
    Gemini-->>Worker: Return Risk Score
    alt Risk Score >= 70%
        Worker->>DB: Update Goal Status (AT_RISK)
        Worker->>Gemini: generateRecoveryPlan()
        Gemini-->>Worker: Return Suggestions & Revised Tasks
        Worker->>DB: Save Revised Tasks & Recovery Suggestions
        Worker->>DB: Save Notification (Recovery Ready)
        Worker-->>User: Push Recovery Web Notification
    else Risk Score < 70%
        Worker->>DB: Goal Status remains ACTIVE
    end
    Note over User, Client: User completes all tasks (Progress: 100%)
    User->>Client: Mark Goal Completed
    Client->>Client: Trigger Confetti Animation
```

### 6.1 Initialization
The user registers and logs in. They navigate to the goal creation page and enter their objective (e.g., "Build MVP for Hackathon") and deadline. Upon submission, a transaction saves the goal as `DRAFT` and queues the setup tasks.

### 6.2 Analysis & Planning
The background worker picks up the job. It invokes the Goal Analyzer and the Planning Agent sequentially. Tasks are created and saved, and the goal status is updated to `PLANNED`. The user receives a push notification confirming the plan is ready.

### 6.3 Daily Execution & Check-ins
The goal status updates to `ACTIVE`. As the user works, they mark tasks as completed and log daily progress check-ins. These logs populate the database with metrics like hours remaining and blocker status.

### 6.4 Active Background Monitoring
Every hour, the background worker sweeps active goals. It checks for inactivity (no updates in 24 hours) and invokes the Risk Agent. The Risk Agent updates the goal's risk score and, if necessary, triggers the Recovery Agent to modify pending tasks. It also runs the Standup Coach once daily to prepare the user's morning briefing.

### 6.5 Project Completion
Once the user completes the final task and submits a check-in showing 100% progress, the frontend displays the confetti animation. The goal status is updated to `COMPLETED`.

